Sentencas: Stefan-Maxwell model (SMM) and simple Fick's model (FM) type of relations both including Knudsen diffusion for the calculation of species mole fraction distribution inside the porous anode of a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) were compared and it was found that at low current densities the models agree well but as current increases the differences also increase.
Titulo: On modeling multi-component diffusion inside the porous anode of solid oxide fuel cells using Fick's model

Sentencas: Based on the findings an empirical correction is proposed for the effective diffusivity used in Fick's model.
Titulo: On modeling multi-component diffusion inside the porous anode of solid oxide fuel cells using Fick's model

Sentencas: The corrected diffusivity coefficient gave better agreement with the Stefan-Maxwell model and even at higher current densities the error is less than 5%.
Titulo: On modeling multi-component diffusion inside the porous anode of solid oxide fuel cells using Fick's model

Sentencas: This correction was implemented via a three-dimensional, in-house SOFC simulation code (DREAMSOFC) which uses Fick's model type relations for diffusion flux calculations.
Titulo: On modeling multi-component diffusion inside the porous anode of solid oxide fuel cells using Fick's model

Sentencas: The code also takes into account methane steam reforming (MSR) and water gas shift (WGS) reactions and the electrochemical oxidation of both H-2 and CO.
Titulo: On modeling multi-component diffusion inside the porous anode of solid oxide fuel cells using Fick's model

Sentencas: As ail application, a SOFC button cell which is being tested at West Virginia University was simulated.
Titulo: On modeling multi-component diffusion inside the porous anode of solid oxide fuel cells using Fick's model

Sentencas: The results with and without the proposed correction for effective diffusivity are compared.
Titulo: On modeling multi-component diffusion inside the porous anode of solid oxide fuel cells using Fick's model
